Watch on youtube: https://youtu.be/VbF1a1_D2eA Tags: 3dprint , material test , azurefilm , In one of my previous videos, I tested AzureFilm PLA Prime, which can be annealed with minimal deformation. Very interesting material. In this video, two more filaments from their Prime line are tested: ABS and ASA. They have the same price, and I am trying to figure out, why they have the ABS next to ASA (since ASA is UV and weather resistant, less smell during the printing).
